### IMPORTANT
Pre-2025-11 model. Baseline-only. Do NOT integrate into production, only benchmark.

## Purpose
Provide historical baseline for speed/quality comparison. all-MiniLM-L6-v2 is the
most widely-used small embedding model and the de facto standard benchmark reference.

## Model Details
- Source: sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
- Parameters: 22.7M (6 transformer layers)
- Dimensions: 384 (fixed, no MRL)
- Context: 512 tokens (truncates longer inputs)
- MTEB: ~49 on retrieval tasks
- Speed: ~5-15ms per batch on CPU

## Architecture (implements Embedder trait as baseline)
```rust
pub struct MiniLmEmbedder {
    session: ort::Session,
    tokenizer: tokenizers::Tokenizer,
    dimensions: usize,    // 384
    max_length: usize,    // 512
    name: String,
}

impl Embedder for MiniLmEmbedder {
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        // Standard transformer embedding pipeline:
        // 1. Tokenize (WordPiece)
        // 2. Pad to max length in batch
        // 3. ONNX forward pass
        // 4. Mean pool last hidden state
        // 5. L2 normalize
        let encodings = self.tokenizer.encode_batch(texts.to_vec(), true)?;
        let max_len = encodings.iter().map(|e| e.len()).max().unwrap_or(0).min(self.max_length);

        let input_ids = build_padded_tensor(&encodings, max_len, 0);
        let attention_mask = build_attention_mask(&encodings, max_len);
        let token_type_ids = build_zeros_tensor(texts.len(), max_len);

        let outputs = self.session.run(ort::inputs![
            "input_ids" => input_ids,
            "attention_mask" => attention_mask,
            "token_type_ids" => token_type_ids,
        ]?)?;

        let hidden = outputs[0].extract_tensor::<f32>()?;
        let mut results = Vec::with_capacity(texts.len());
        for i in 0..texts.len() {
            let mut pooled = mean_pool_with_mask(&hidden, i, max_len, self.dimensions, &attention_mask);
            l2_normalize(&mut pooled);
            results.push(pooled);
        }
        Ok(results)
    }

    fn dimensions(&self) -> usize { 384 }
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn supports_mrl(&self) -> bool { false }
}
```

